{
  "texts": [
    "The most interesting case is at ν = -2 since this is near the fillings where superconductivity is most prominent.",
    "Taking the VH state as an example, a ferromagnetic (anti-ferromagnetic) Hund's coupling would lead to a spin-ferromagnetic (spin-valley-locked) state.",
    "This distinction is crucial for constraining the properties of the proximate superconducting domes, if the correlated insulator is indeed the parent state.",
    "Recent experiments have addressed this using electron spin resonance [165] and twist-decoupled heterostructures [270].",
    "These studies suggest that the Hund's coupling is anti-ferromagnetic."
  ]
}